By modifying the interviewer email address parameter within a valid rescheduling workflow, an attacker could access the available interview slots of interviewers outside the scope of the intended scheduling process. This results in unauthorized disclosure of internal scheduling information due to insufficient access control enforcement.

Open a valid interview rescheduling link received via email.
Navigate to the functionality that retrieves available interview slots.
Intercept the request using a proxy tool.
Identify the parameter containing the interviewer's email address.
Replace the email address with that of another interviewer.
Forward the modified request to the server.
Observe that the application returns the availability information of the unauthorized interviewer.
